  "number": 116,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/116",
  "title": "API proposal: `transformData` before template rendering",
  "body": "Following discussion in #72 .\n\nIn a lot of wigets, there are many reasons that could justify modifying the data before calling the `render` method of the template: formatting, adding lambdas, etc. Right now, we're doing it by passing a function to `template`, however it doesn't seem logical that data modification happens there.\n\nA solution that could make sense would be to add an optional `transformData` parameter to the object passed to a widget constructor which would accept a callback.\n\nThis callback would accept one object parameter: the previously object sent to `render`.  \nIt would then return a new (or not) object to be used with the `render` method.\n\n``` js\ninstantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\n  container: '#myfacet',\n  facetName: 'myfacet',\n  template: '{{ value }}',\n  transformData: function (refinement) {\n    return { value: '$' + refinement.name };\n  }\n});\n```\n\nSome questions:\n- Should we deep clone the object before sending it to `transformData` ?\n- How to handle the _multiple templates_ widgets (e.g. hits)? I am not found of the plural form of `transformsData`, and `transforms` might be clearer. Is there anything else we'd like to transform ?\n",
